com.cmput301f19t09.vibes.models

Class MoodEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cmput301f19t09.vibes.models.Event
      • com.cmput301f19t09.vibes.models.MoodEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.google.maps.android.clustering.ClusterItem, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable

    public class MoodEvent
extends Event
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable, com.google.maps.android.clustering.ClusterItem
    Represents an event relating to a mood. Extends Event to inherit date, time, and description. For a MoodEvent date and time are not optional while description is. MoodEvent also has a non-optional EmotionalState and optional socialSituation and Location. A MoodEvent is associated with a particular User. Implements serializable to be passable in intents. Implements Comparable to allow MoodList to be sorted in reverse chronological order of LocalDateTime of the MoodEvents.

        public MoodEvent(java.time.LocalDate date,
                 java.time.LocalTime time,
                 java.lang.String description,
                 EmotionalState state,
                 int socialSituation,
                 android.net.Uri photo,
                 android.location.Location location,
                 User user)
        Creates a new MoodEvent object by accepting a date, time, description, state, socialSituation, location, and user.
        Parameters:
        date - Date of when the event occurred; should have the format ISO_LOCAL_DATE (yyyy-MM-dd).
        time - Time of when the event occurred; should have the format HH:mm.
        description - Describes the circumstances surrounding an event.
        state - The EmotionalState of a MoodEvent which contains an emotion, emoticon, and associated color.
        socialSituation - The context surrounding an event; can be one of alone, with one other person, with two to several people, or with a crowd.
        photo - Used in part to describe the circumstances of an event. The path to a photo.
        location - Where a MoodEvent occurred; the location should contain latitude and longitude coordinates.
        user - The user that the created the MoodEvent.
